<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12995] Document that HConnection#getTable methods do not check table existence since 0.98.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12995</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jamestaylor&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jamestaylor&quot;&gt;James Taylor&lt;/a&gt; mentioned that recently Phoenix discovered at some point the &lt;tt&gt;HConnection#getTable&lt;/tt&gt; &quot;lightweight table reference&quot; methods stopped throwing TableNotFoundExceptions. It used to be (in 0.94 and 0.96) that all APIs that construct HTables would check if the table is locatable and throw exceptions if not. Now, if using the &lt;tt&gt;HConnection#getTable&lt;/tt&gt; APIs, such exceptions will only be thrown at the time of the first operation submitted using the table reference, should a problem be detected then. We did a bisect and it seems this was changed in the 0.98.1 release by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10080&quot; title=&quot;Unnecessary call to locateRegion when creating an HTable instance&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10080&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-10080&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Since the change has now shipped in 10 in total 0.98 releases we should just document the change, in the javadoc of the HConnection class, Connection in branch-1+. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
